==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taxine
<hw>Tax"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>taxus</ets> a
yew.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A poisonous alkaloid of bitter taste
extracted from the leaves and seeds of the European yew (<spn>Taxus
baccata</spn>). Called also <altname>taxia</altname>. The usual
preparation is a mixture of compounds. Taxine A has the chemical
formula: <chform>C35H47NO10</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taxis</ent>⟦br⟧
